":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Amber Rudd","withdrawn":false,"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/amber-rudd","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/amber-rudd"}],"primary_publishing_organisation":[{"analytics_identifier":"D10","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions","base_path":"/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions","content_id":"b548a09f-8b35-4104-89f4-f1a40bf3136d","document_type":"organisation","locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Department for Work and Pensions","withdrawn":false,"details":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Department<br/>for Work &amp; <br/>Pensions","crest":"single-identity"},"brand":"department-for-work-pensions","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/35/s300_dwp-caxton-house-logo-960.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/35/s960_dwp-caxton-house-logo-960.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions"}],"roles":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions","base_path":"/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions","content_id":"845e6272-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","document_type":"ministerial_role","locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2018-01-10T10:52:23Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Secretary of State for Work and Pensions","withdrawn":false,"details":{"body":"<p>The Secretary of State has overall responsibility for the Department for Work and Pensions (<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>). They have direct responsibility for departmental expenditure and departmental management.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> is responsible for the administration of the State Pension and working age benefits system, providing support to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>people of working age</li>\n  <li>employers</li>\n  <li>pensioners</li>\n  <li>families and children</li>\n  <li>disabled people</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/secretary-of-state-for-work-and-pensions"}],"available_translations":[{"title":"Record number of women in work as wages continue to outstrip inflation","public_updated_at":"2019-08-13T13:59:54Z","document_type":"press_release","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/record-number-of-women-in-work-as-wages-continue-to-outstrip-inflation","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/record-number-of-women-in-work-as-wages-continue-to-outstrip-inflation","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"c08e2dc2-64a4-4f0c-bc18-22048727fd16","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/record-number-of-women-in-work-as-wages-continue-to-outstrip-inflation","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/record-number-of-women-in-work-as-wages-continue-to-outstrip-inflation","links":{}}]},"description":"UK employment rate at joint record high 76.1%, as number in work reaches 32.8 million, and wages surpass inflation for the 17th consecutive month.","details":{"body":"<p>The UK jobs market remains resilient, as statistics out today (13 August 2019) show the number of people in work is at a record high of 32.8 million, a rise of over 3.7 million since 2010.</p>\n\n<figure class=\"image embedded\"><div class=\"img\"><img src=\"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d52b7d5ed915d7645a6a995/lms_0819_employment_gov.png\" alt=\"Employment rate is 76.1%\"></div></figure>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/employmentandemployeetypes/articles/labourmarketeconomiccommentary/august2019\">New figures from the Office for National Statistics</a> also show the UK workforce is more gender diverse than ever before, with the number of women climbing to a new record high and ethnic minority employment rate at a near record high, now making up 51% and 32% of employment growth respectively since 2010.</p>\n\n<p>Sectors such as manufacturing and construction are experiencing the big increase in number of jobs, with 85,000 more people employed in the last year.</p>\n\n<p>Wages are also on the up this month outstripping inflation for a 17th month, boosting consumer confidence and spending power for millions â€“ with real term total wage growth hitting 1.8%.</p>\n\n<p>Meanwhile UK unemployment rate remains steady at 3.9% - as the number of unemployed people continues fall in every region of the UK since 2010.</p>\n\n<figure class=\"image embedded\"><div class=\"img\"><img src=\"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d52b81640f0b642c442db3c/lms_0819_unmployment_gov.png\" alt=\"Unemployment rate is 3.9%\"></div></figure>\n\n<p>Todayâ€™s statistics also show the number of disabled people in work increasing by 1.15 million in the last 6 years â€“ and an increase of 246,000 disabled people in employment in the last year.</p>\n\n<p>Secretary of State for Work and Pensions and Minister for Women and Equalities, Amber Rudd said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>More people in work than ever before means more households across the UK are earning a regular income, and millions more receiving a pay boost thanks to wages rising at their fastest in a decade â€“ outstripping inflation for a 17th month in a row.</p>\n\n  <p>Our workforce increasingly reflects our vibrant society, with a record number of women in employment while the number out of work falls to an all-time low.</p>\n\n  <p class=\"last-child\">This week many young people will receive their A level results and begin their career journey. They should know that they are entering a workforce that is flourishing and full of opportunity and I hope all young people, especially women, feel empowered to flourish in every role in every sector.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>The government is helping even more people benefit from a well-paid job by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>backing businesses to create good jobs with the modern <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/topical-events/the-uks-industrial-strategy\">Industrial Strategy</a> â€“ including strengthening workersâ€™ rights, and tightening the rules for big businesses</li>\n  <li>investing in infrastructure, training and apprenticeships we need for our future, with public investment at its highest in 40 years</li>\n  <li>introducing Universal Credit â€“ better supporting people move into work faster and stay in it longer</li>\n  <li>supporting employers to recruit, re-train and retain older workers to stay in work longer with our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/fuller-working-lives-a-partnership-approach\">Fuller Working Lives strategy</a>\n</li>\n  <li>tackling employment inequalities with targeted support in 20 UK regions and Â£90 million to help support young people</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"contact-press-office\">Contact Press Office</h2>\n\n<p>Media enquiries for this press release â€“ 020 3267 5144</p>\n\n<div id=\"contact_df0a78d2-6122-46ac-8014-6f8c5e0b8d3f\" class=\"contact postal-address\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Press Office</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n      <p class=\"adr\">\n<span class=\"street-address\">Caxton House\n<br>\nTothill Street</span><br>\n<span class=\"locality\">London</span><br>\n<span class=\"postal-code\">SW1H 9NA</span>\n</p>\n\n    \n    \n      <div class=\"email-url-number\">\n      \n      \n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">London Press Office (national media and London area enquiries only â€“ not questions about personal claims)</span>\n          020 3267 5144\n        </p>\n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Out-of-hours (journalists only)</span>\n          07623 928 975\n        </p>\n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">England and Wales (local media enquiries)</span>\n          029 20 586 then 097 or 098 or 099\n        </p>\n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Scotland (local media enquiries)</span>\n          0131 310 1122\n        </p>\n      \n      </div>\n    \n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p>Follow DWP on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.twitter.com/dwppressoffice\">Twitter</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/dwp\">Facebook</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/dwp\">LinkedIn</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/dwp\">YouTube</a></li>\n</ul>\n","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-08-13T13:24:03.065Z"}]},"document_status":"published_but_needs_2i","created_by":"Joe Brown","last_updated_by":"Reinhold Messner","political":true,"government":{"title":"2015 Conservative government","slug":"2015-conservative-government","start_date":"2015-05-07T23:00:00.000Z","end_date":"","current":true},"document_schema":"news"}